==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misrepresentation
<hw>Mis*rep`re*sen*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Untrue
representation; false or incorrect statement or account; -- usually
unfavorable to the thing represented; <as>as, a
<ex>misrepresentation</ex> of a person's motives</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Sydney Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In popular use, this word often conveys the idea of
intentional untruth.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misrepresentative</ent>⟦br⟧
